2
00:01:03.497 --> 00:01:06.834
You managed to get most of it
on the paper this time.

3
00:01:08.269 --> 00:01:09.803
Good job. buddy.

4
00:01:11.172 --> 00:01:12.541
Okay.

5
00:01:13.107 --> 00:01:14.675
<i>Hey. hey. it's me.</i>

6
00:01:15.476 --> 00:01:16.877
<i>Happy birthday week.</i>

7
00:01:17.011 --> 00:01:18.513
<i>So. I expect</i>
<i>you're celebrating.</i>

8
00:01:18.647 --> 00:01:20.147
<i>When do you think</i>
<i>you're coming back?</i>

9
00:01:20.281 --> 00:01:21.749
<i>Let me know. 'Cause. well.</i>
<i>you know. we miss you.</i>

10
00:01:21.882 --> 00:01:22.950
<i>Okay. don't have too much--</i>

11
00:01:49.678 --> 00:01:52.279
I need a yellow sun. like. now.

12
00:03:13.561 --> 00:03:14.529
Brigands.

13
00:03:15.963 --> 00:03:17.331
They've come for my swords.

14
00:03:17.464 --> 00:03:19.333
I guess it was only
a matter of time.

15
00:03:19.701 --> 00:03:21.201
We give them what they want...

16
00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:24.405
and then they'll leave.

17
00:04:08.982 --> 00:04:10.217
Mm?

18
00:04:12.853 --> 00:04:13.621
Is that pie?

19
00:04:16.791 --> 00:04:17.458
Yes.

20
00:04:45.018 --> 00:04:46.521
I know who you are.

21
00:04:48.656 --> 00:04:50.290
Krem of the Yellow Hills.

22
00:04:50.792 --> 00:04:52.493
Then you know why I'm here.

23
00:04:52.627 --> 00:04:54.061
My life's work.

24
00:04:54.928 --> 00:04:56.196
All in the shed out back.

25
00:04:56.330 --> 00:04:57.498
Handcrafted weapons

26
00:04:57.632 --> 00:04:59.066
forged from
the strongest steel

27
00:04:59.199 --> 00:05:00.234
that you or your Brigand army

28
00:05:00.367 --> 00:05:02.302
will ever lay
your filthy eyes on.

29
00:05:02.436 --> 00:05:05.239
You have what you want.
Now leave.

30
00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:19.486
Show me the way.

31
00:05:20.387 --> 00:05:22.022
Not you.

32
00:05:23.792 --> 00:05:25.325
Her.

33
00:05:34.702 --> 00:05:36.270
No!

34
00:05:57.991 --> 00:05:59.960
Mm-hmm.

35
00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:43.738
I. Kara Zor-El.

36
00:06:43.872 --> 00:06:48.776
of inebriated mind. body.

37
00:06:48.910 --> 00:06:51.044
and. uh... spirit...

38
00:06:51.178 --> 00:06:53.715
I hereby declare...

39
00:06:55.517 --> 00:06:57.852
that 23 will be
the best year yet.

40
00:06:58.318 --> 00:06:59.486
But let's be honest. babe.

41
00:06:59.621 --> 00:07:02.022
it's not a very high bar
to clear.

42
00:07:07.929 --> 00:07:09.062
Okay...

43
00:07:10.364 --> 00:07:11.666
Should we just move here?

44
00:07:11.799 --> 00:07:14.334
Maybe we're meant to be
red sun folks. you know?

45
00:07:14.468 --> 00:07:18.405
The kinds who feel things like
a punch in the face

46
00:07:18.540 --> 00:07:21.241
and. like. shots of. like.
whatever this is.

47
00:07:23.143 --> 00:07:24.546
It's really good. you know?

48
00:07:27.180 --> 00:07:28.448
Maybe this is home.

49
00:07:56.343 --> 00:07:57.512
Not gonna happen.

50
00:08:17.331 --> 00:08:18.498
Attention.

51
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:21.869
Attention!

52
00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:28.509
Seriously?

53
00:08:28.643 --> 00:08:31.079
I am Ruthye Marye Knoll
of the Danastia Clan.

54
00:08:31.278 --> 00:08:32.914
And I come here
with one purpose.

55
00:08:33.047 --> 00:08:34.381
Man.

56
00:08:34.515 --> 00:08:36.149
To seek revenge against
Krem of the Yellow Hills...

57
00:08:37.685 --> 00:08:39.319
...a Brigand who has
trespassed onto our planet.

58
00:08:39.453 --> 00:08:41.355
murdered my innocent
and honorable family

59
00:08:41.488 --> 00:08:43.323
-in cold blood.
-Rough.

60
00:08:43.457 --> 00:08:45.526
Krem's ship was destroyed.
and I believe

61
00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:47.294
he's still searching for
a passage off our planet.

62
00:08:47.427 --> 00:08:49.097
I will need a skilled tracker.

63
00:08:49.229 --> 00:08:50.598
who can help me locate
this monster

64
00:08:50.732 --> 00:08:53.001
-before he escapes.
-Dude. no.

65
00:08:53.133 --> 00:08:55.937
I don't-- I don't have
my powers here. all right?

66
00:08:56.070 --> 00:08:57.905
- I will do the rest...
- Not my monkeys.

67
00:08:58.039 --> 00:08:59.206
Not my circus.

68
00:08:59.339 --> 00:09:00.842
...ending his life
to avenge my family.

69
00:09:03.911 --> 00:09:05.245
In exchange...

70
00:09:07.015 --> 00:09:08.683
I offer you my family sword.

71
00:09:09.383 --> 00:09:11.919
Made by the hands
of my father. Elias Knoll.

72
00:09:13.286 --> 00:09:14.656
The blade will be
provided to you

73
00:09:14.789 --> 00:09:16.591
after I use it
to take Krem's life.

74
00:09:19.027 --> 00:09:20.327
It's not our problem.

75
00:09:20.460 --> 00:09:23.196
-Elias Knoll. you say?
-Yes.

76
00:09:24.899 --> 00:09:27.501
A child of your size expects
to wield such a weapon?

77
00:09:27.635 --> 00:09:28.736
I am no child.

78
00:09:28.870 --> 00:09:30.872
I had my thirteenth turn
this past harvest.

79
00:09:31.005 --> 00:09:33.373
Ah. but taking on a Brigand?

80
00:09:33.875 --> 00:09:36.644
-Impossible.
-Oh. that might be a problem.

81
00:09:36.778 --> 00:09:39.914
You will need someone of
enormous power to defeat Krem.

82
00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:41.348
I shall do the job myself.

83
00:09:48.422 --> 00:09:52.325
Hey!

84
00:09:53.728 --> 00:09:54.996
Mm-mm.

85
00:09:55.129 --> 00:09:58.198
Hold this. All right. just...
Let me talk to him.

86
00:10:02.269 --> 00:10:04.672
It's not too late.

87
00:10:06.507 --> 00:10:09.342
Let's not... be a jerk.

88
00:10:09.744 --> 00:10:11.913
Just... Just give me back
the sword-- Whoa.

89
00:10:13.648 --> 00:10:15.282
...and we can move on.

90
00:10:15.415 --> 00:10:17.451
You don't steal
from a little kid

91
00:10:17.585 --> 00:10:19.854
who just lost her parents.
Like. that's--

92
00:10:20.287 --> 00:10:22.156
Man. that's so clearly
over the line

93
00:10:22.289 --> 00:10:23.891
of acceptable behavior.

94
00:10:27.662 --> 00:10:29.797
You could at least
help her find the...

95
00:10:30.698 --> 00:10:31.566
God.

96
00:10:31.699 --> 00:10:33.400
...find the shithead
who killed them.

97
00:10:33.534 --> 00:10:34.535
and then you can get
the sword.

98
00:10:34.669 --> 00:10:35.903
like. fair and square.

99
00:10:37.772 --> 00:10:39.807
Oh. you think
I'm talking too much?

100
00:10:39.941 --> 00:10:40.942
No problem.

101
00:10:41.976 --> 00:10:43.144
I can talk less.

102
00:10:50.051 --> 00:10:51.953
Okay. that was...
that was less talking.

103
00:10:52.720 --> 00:10:54.055
How do you like that?

104
00:10:54.188 --> 00:10:55.690
Oh. God! There it is. Wow.

105
00:10:55.990 --> 00:10:57.324
Okay.

106
00:10:57.457 --> 00:10:59.761
It's actually. like. a really
beautiful piece of silverware.

107
00:11:07.869 --> 00:11:09.971
Hey. look. I'm bleeding.

108
00:11:10.938 --> 00:11:11.873
Whoa!

109
00:11:13.306 --> 00:11:14.742
Whoa. what the fu--?

110
00:11:16.711 --> 00:11:18.746
Oh. you're an angry fella.
aren't you?

111
00:11:34.896 --> 00:11:37.297
Easy. Okay. Okay!
Give me a second.

112
00:11:37.430 --> 00:11:38.533
I'm a little...
I'm a little winded.

113
00:11:39.366 --> 00:11:40.467
No. no. no. no. no.

114
00:11:42.469 --> 00:11:43.604
Argh!

115
00:11:58.485 --> 00:11:59.954
Whew.

116
00:12:13.668 --> 00:12:15.102
Believe this is yours.

117
00:12:19.472 --> 00:12:20.608
Thank you.

118
00:12:23.476 --> 00:12:24.712
I need to go to bed.

119
00:12:34.322 --> 00:12:35.957
Stop. Stop.

120
00:12:50.972 --> 00:12:51.906
Oh.

121
00:12:53.241 --> 00:12:54.374
Um...

122
00:13:00.214 --> 00:13:01.249
Ow!

123
00:13:01.682 --> 00:13:04.384
Oh...

124
00:13:06.053 --> 00:13:06.988
Ugh.

125
00:13:20.735 --> 00:13:22.370
<i>Hi! Hi. Finally got you.</i>

126
00:13:22.502 --> 00:13:24.839
Mm-hmm. It's my lucky day!

127
00:13:24.972 --> 00:13:27.041
<i>Still. uh...</i>
<i>still celebrating. huh?</i>

128
00:13:27.174 --> 00:13:28.342
Yeah. What do you want?

129
00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:31.112
<i>I was just... Just wanted</i>
<i>to touch base about</i>

130
00:13:31.245 --> 00:13:32.647
<i>when you think</i>
<i>you might be coming back.</i>

131
00:13:33.247 --> 00:13:34.248
No idea.

132
00:13:34.382 --> 00:13:35.850
<i>Kara. I'm just worried that...</i>

133
00:13:35.983 --> 00:13:37.718
<i>if you keep going off-planet</i>
<i>like this.</i>

134
00:13:37.852 --> 00:13:39.120
<i>you're never gonna find</i>
<i>your stride here.</i>

135
00:13:39.253 --> 00:13:40.221
<i>in Metropolis.</i>

136
00:13:40.354 --> 00:13:41.722
Hold on.

137
00:13:41.856 --> 00:13:43.791
<i>I'm worried you might never</i>
<i>find your people.</i>

138
00:13:45.059 --> 00:13:48.596
Mm. That's the thing. Clark.
I have no people.

139
00:13:49.263 --> 00:13:50.497
<i>I know that.</i>

140
00:13:50.631 --> 00:13:52.733
<i>I just mean maybe if you spent</i>
<i>a little more time here.</i>

141
00:13:52.867 --> 00:13:54.368
<i>you might feel more at home.</i>

142
00:13:54.501 --> 00:13:57.238
Hold on! Uh. I gotta go.

143
00:13:57.371 --> 00:13:59.273
<i>Okay. Just. um. give me a call</i>
<i>and let me know--</i>

144
00:13:59.407 --> 00:14:00.508
Good talk. Bye.

145
00:14:01.976 --> 00:14:03.476
Hold on!

146
00:14:05.947 --> 00:14:08.115
I am Ruthye Marye Knoll
of the Danastia Clan.

147
00:14:08.783 --> 00:14:09.984
And I come here
to seek revenge--

148
00:14:10.117 --> 00:14:11.886
Yeah. some guy named Cream.
Yeah.

149
00:14:12.019 --> 00:14:13.754
You already hit me
with this pitch.

150
00:14:13.888 --> 00:14:16.023
So. what. you're going...

151
00:14:17.490 --> 00:14:18.993
You're door-to-door now?

152
00:14:19.126 --> 00:14:21.963
Look. I would love
to help you. but I can't.

153
00:14:22.096 --> 00:14:24.432
So. onto the next door
with you.

154
00:14:26.033 --> 00:14:28.936
Now. if you'll excuse me.
I really need to pee.

155
00:14:29.070 --> 00:14:30.137
Okay.

156
00:14:45.485 --> 00:14:46.988
-Was your ship attacked?
-Oh. my God.

157
00:14:49.256 --> 00:14:51.125
Wait! Please!

158
00:14:51.792 --> 00:14:54.161
Look. last night you stood up
for the righteous.

159
00:14:54.295 --> 00:14:55.495
The just.

160
00:14:55.629 --> 00:14:56.797
Look...

161
00:14:57.431 --> 00:14:58.966
If you think I'm gonna
lead you on the mountains

162
00:14:59.100 --> 00:15:01.902
through some sort of...
revenge plot.

163
00:15:02.036 --> 00:15:05.606
turning you into
a psychotic... child murderer.

164
00:15:05.740 --> 00:15:08.776
then you must be. as they say.
"on glue."

165
00:15:10.344 --> 00:15:11.879
Ew.

166
00:15:26.961 --> 00:15:29.563
Shall we take Elias' daughter?

167
00:15:30.031 --> 00:15:32.400
The cells are packed solid.
aren't they?

168
00:15:35.703 --> 00:15:38.139
What do you think
of my new ship?

169
00:15:41.776 --> 00:15:42.877
Come on. man.

170
00:15:43.010 --> 00:15:44.945
We gotta be
back up in the sky ASAP.

171
00:15:45.346 --> 00:15:46.947
Krem deserves
what is coming to him.

172
00:15:48.482 --> 00:15:50.885
You go round driven by "deserve"
and you'll end up...

173
00:15:51.552 --> 00:15:52.686
very unhappy.

174
00:16:04.065 --> 00:16:05.800
Krypto!

175
00:16:05.933 --> 00:16:07.701
- Krem. That's him.
- What the--? Hey!

176
00:16:07.835 --> 00:16:09.070
They're taking your ship
off the planet.

177
00:16:10.204 --> 00:16:11.305
Krypto!

178
00:16:15.142 --> 00:16:16.811
No! Krypto!

179
00:16:17.678 --> 00:16:18.846
No!

180
00:16:30.491 --> 00:16:32.493
Hey. Hey. buddy.

181
00:16:33.094 --> 00:16:35.162
It's gonna be okay. Okay?

182
00:16:54.715 --> 00:16:56.150
A Brigandian toxin

183
00:16:56.283 --> 00:16:57.118
known as Reddimeir.

184
00:16:57.251 --> 00:16:59.920
She says it paralyzes
the host slowly.

185
00:17:00.054 --> 00:17:01.755
and I'm sorry. but painfully.

186
00:17:01.889 --> 00:17:03.257
before eventually...

187
00:17:04.058 --> 00:17:05.192
stopping the heart.

188
00:17:06.694 --> 00:17:07.862
What can I do?

189
00:17:10.631 --> 00:17:11.832
What? What is it?

190
00:17:13.568 --> 00:17:14.735
She says it's more difficult

191
00:17:14.869 --> 00:17:16.637
since Krem escaped
off the planet.

192
00:17:16.770 --> 00:17:18.806
Moving him
would risk accelerating

193
00:17:18.939 --> 00:17:20.509
the effects of the toxin.

194
00:17:21.041 --> 00:17:22.977
The Brigands carry
the antidote on their person.

195
00:17:25.514 --> 00:17:28.349
They use it
as an interrogation tactic.

196
00:17:28.482 --> 00:17:31.285
Dangling relief
in exchange for money.

197
00:17:31.752 --> 00:17:34.288
information.
whatever they're after.

198
00:17:38.792 --> 00:17:39.793
Without the antidote

199
00:17:39.927 --> 00:17:41.162
there's nothing she can do.

200
00:17:42.564 --> 00:17:43.731
How long does he have?

201
00:17:45.900 --> 00:17:47.268
Three moon raises.

202
00:17:48.836 --> 00:17:51.238
Okay. Three days.

203
00:17:53.107 --> 00:17:56.744
Hey. Hey.
I'm gonna go now.

204
00:18:00.381 --> 00:18:03.784
And you-- You cannot
freaking give up on me.

205
00:18:05.654 --> 00:18:07.221
Home is
wherever you are. buddy.

206
00:18:19.833 --> 00:18:21.869
Are you going after Krem
for the antidote?

207
00:18:22.604 --> 00:18:23.672
You could help me.

208
00:18:23.804 --> 00:18:25.206
No. we could help each other.

209
00:18:25.339 --> 00:18:28.842
You for the antidote.
and me to kill him.

210
00:18:29.743 --> 00:18:32.713
Look. I'm... I'm sorry...

211
00:18:33.247 --> 00:18:34.516
about what happened
to your family.

212
00:18:34.649 --> 00:18:36.217
Okay? I am. So he'll suffer.

213
00:18:36.350 --> 00:18:37.718
Suffer?
No. he needs to be killed.

214
00:18:37.851 --> 00:18:40.020
Ruthye. your revenge
is not going to get in the way

215
00:18:40.154 --> 00:18:41.789
of me saving my dog.

216
00:18:43.390 --> 00:18:46.026
Okay. just... like. just
stay here and look after him.

217
00:19:01.809 --> 00:19:02.977
Okay.

218
00:19:03.844 --> 00:19:05.379
One...

219
00:19:05.513 --> 00:19:06.615
Two...

220
00:19:07.181 --> 00:19:09.783
Three... moon raises.

221
00:19:11.352 --> 00:19:13.854
72 hours. buddy.

222
00:19:31.972 --> 00:19:33.508
Who are you?

223
00:20:03.571 --> 00:20:04.673
He basically
said. "Welcome aboard.

224
00:20:04.805 --> 00:20:05.774
Please watch your step."

225
00:20:05.906 --> 00:20:08.142
Yeah. sure he did.

226
00:20:34.736 --> 00:20:35.869
Gum?

227
00:20:42.744 --> 00:20:46.146
Maybe give us all a break
from that hookah thingy.

228
00:20:48.415 --> 00:20:49.551
Okay.

229
00:20:50.217 --> 00:20:52.386
Comfy?

230
00:20:55.022 --> 00:20:56.190
You got a clue
what I'm saying?

231
00:20:57.391 --> 00:20:59.393
Do I look like an idiot
to you?

232
00:21:00.829 --> 00:21:01.895
Debatable.

233
00:21:02.029 --> 00:21:03.531
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to.

234
00:21:03.665 --> 00:21:05.299
I was just trying
to get through to my seat.

235
00:21:05.432 --> 00:21:07.669
-It was an accident.
-Oh. freakin' Ruthye.

236
00:21:13.474 --> 00:21:14.875
Ow.

237
00:21:24.118 --> 00:21:25.520
You put your bag on the floor
at her feet.

238
00:21:25.653 --> 00:21:28.021
which is calling her mother
a whore.

239
00:21:28.556 --> 00:21:31.793
Okay. why aren't you
with Krypto?

240
00:21:31.925 --> 00:21:33.327
I'm searching for Krem myself.

241
00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:37.498
I think I was pretty clear
when I said no to that plan.

242
00:21:39.066 --> 00:21:40.234
Excuse me. can you move over

243
00:21:40.367 --> 00:21:41.736
so I can sit
next to my friend?

244
00:21:41.870 --> 00:21:43.904
Oh. your friend. Absolutely.

245
00:21:44.037 --> 00:21:45.272
She's not my fr...
You're not my friend.

246
00:21:45.406 --> 00:21:46.373
Yes. I am.

247
00:21:48.409 --> 00:21:49.376
Okay.

248
00:21:50.911 --> 00:21:53.180
-What's my name?
-What?

249
00:21:55.449 --> 00:21:57.951
What did you hit now. Lloyd?

250
00:22:14.468 --> 00:22:15.537
Who are they?

251
00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:16.671
What do they want?

252
00:22:16.805 --> 00:22:18.138
Sklarian Raiders.

253
00:22:18.272 --> 00:22:20.040
They're like tech pirates.

254
00:22:20.675 --> 00:22:22.577
They want the bus.
they want the fuel.

255
00:22:22.710 --> 00:22:23.611
they want the engine.

256
00:22:23.745 --> 00:22:25.814
Look away. Lloyd.
Look away. Look away.

257
00:22:26.447 --> 00:22:28.683
My guess is they want
to rob us all blind first.

258
00:22:53.808 --> 00:22:55.108
Noted.

259
00:22:55.242 --> 00:22:57.244
I knew I should have
called in sick today. Lloyd.

260
00:23:03.250 --> 00:23:04.084
The watch.

261
00:23:24.438 --> 00:23:26.741
No. she doesn't--
You know. she doesn't--

262
00:23:26.875 --> 00:23:28.676
Ruthye. Ruthye. let go.

263
00:23:28.810 --> 00:23:31.713
Ruthye. let go. Let go.

264
00:23:33.781 --> 00:23:36.684
Between you and me.
the sword...

265
00:23:36.818 --> 00:23:38.485
It's not worth much. you know.
See--

266
00:23:47.361 --> 00:23:49.162
I have a plan.

267
00:23:51.766 --> 00:23:52.800
Kind of.

268
00:23:53.902 --> 00:23:55.537
Hey!

269
00:23:55.970 --> 00:23:57.605
You ladies wanna trade?

270
00:23:58.438 --> 00:23:59.874
'Cause I would love
that watch and sword back.

271
00:24:00.008 --> 00:24:02.744
and I'm pretty sure that
you would be interested...

272
00:24:02.877 --> 00:24:04.177
in this.

273
00:24:04.979 --> 00:24:06.514
Oh. sorry. wrong pocket.

274
00:24:06.648 --> 00:24:07.715
In this.

275
00:24:17.692 --> 00:24:19.761
Whoa. Oh. shit.

276
00:24:24.364 --> 00:24:27.301
Uh. just getting my sea legs.

277
00:24:35.342 --> 00:24:37.177
Shit.

278
00:24:41.415 --> 00:24:43.051
Okay.
this is unpleasant.

279
00:25:11.244 --> 00:25:14.247
Hey. Hey. uh...

280
00:25:14.381 --> 00:25:16.618
How... How close are we
to a yellow sun?

281
00:25:27.829 --> 00:25:29.530
Can you get any closer?

282
00:25:29.664 --> 00:25:31.431
Yeah. sure. If I had
a friggin' engine

283
00:25:31.566 --> 00:25:34.501
or some balls.
but I have neither. So. no.

284
00:25:37.839 --> 00:25:40.173
Perfect. Um...

285
00:25:54.589 --> 00:25:55.923
Shhh.

286
00:25:56.057 --> 00:25:57.625
Ooh. this is gonna be bad.

287
00:26:01.194 --> 00:26:02.295
Come on.

288
00:26:16.844 --> 00:26:18.178
Oh. shi--

289
00:27:49.704 --> 00:27:50.772
She's flying towards the sun!

290
00:28:54.635 --> 00:28:55.636
We've lost our engines!

291
00:28:57.337 --> 00:28:58.873
Found them.

292
00:29:33.875 --> 00:29:34.909
When I asked for your help.

293
00:29:35.042 --> 00:29:36.611
I did not know
you were so capable.

294
00:29:36.744 --> 00:29:39.446
Yeah. You won the lottery.

295
00:29:39.580 --> 00:29:40.915
Why couldn't you do that
on my planet?

296
00:29:41.048 --> 00:29:43.351
I get my powers
from the yellow sun.

297
00:29:43.483 --> 00:29:46.453
The... red sun
makes me normal.

298
00:29:47.021 --> 00:29:48.522
Then why would you choose
to be under a red sun?

299
00:29:48.656 --> 00:29:50.124
Well. 'cause the whiskey
don't work so good

300
00:29:50.258 --> 00:29:51.391
when I'm like this.

301
00:29:52.526 --> 00:29:54.061
With abilities like that.

302
00:29:54.195 --> 00:29:55.663
you're sure to be able
to take on Krem.

303
00:29:55.796 --> 00:29:58.633
Enough! You're coming with me
to find Krem.

304
00:29:58.766 --> 00:30:01.836
Congratulations.
You wore me down.

305
00:30:03.470 --> 00:30:05.106
You were gonna do it
either way.

306
00:30:05.573 --> 00:30:07.141
At best
you'll end up kidnapped.

307
00:30:07.275 --> 00:30:09.076
At worst you'll screw it up
for the both of us.

308
00:30:09.210 --> 00:30:11.478
and... oh. I've got
to save my dog.

309
00:30:12.280 --> 00:30:14.447
Just do what I say.

310
00:30:14.582 --> 00:30:16.617
Keep quiet and don't die.

311
00:30:16.751 --> 00:30:18.953
There she is.
It's flying sun lady.

312
00:30:19.086 --> 00:30:20.721
Good job.
We kicked ass back there. huh?

313
00:30:20.855 --> 00:30:22.189
We make a good team. I think.

314
00:30:22.323 --> 00:30:23.758
We're wondering if you could
help us find the Brigands.

315
00:30:23.891 --> 00:30:24.892
Do you have any idea
where they are?

316
00:30:25.026 --> 00:30:26.160
No idea.

317
00:30:26.294 --> 00:30:28.162
But I bet those Sklarians
that you tied up on my bus

318
00:30:28.296 --> 00:30:29.630
probably do.

319
00:30:29.764 --> 00:30:31.399
See. that is an idea.

320
00:30:31.532 --> 00:30:34.201
Here's an even better idea:
Don't abandon your daughter.

321
00:30:38.873 --> 00:30:40.641
These taste like shit.
Um. okay.

322
00:30:41.842 --> 00:30:43.476
I really don't have time
for this. so...

323
00:30:43.611 --> 00:30:45.179
...let's get to it.

324
00:30:46.881 --> 00:30:48.516
Oh. it's okay. Don't worry.

325
00:30:48.649 --> 00:30:50.450
I'll do the other side
to even it out...

326
00:30:50.584 --> 00:30:52.320
if you tell me
where to find Krem.

327
00:30:52.920 --> 00:30:54.255
And what will you give us
in return?

328
00:30:54.388 --> 00:30:55.423
Oh. that's a good question.

329
00:30:55.556 --> 00:30:57.124
Um...

330
00:30:59.492 --> 00:31:00.962
An intact spinal cord.

331
00:31:01.529 --> 00:31:02.697
So you gonna talk or...

332
00:31:03.397 --> 00:31:04.699
Let her have him.

333
00:31:04.832 --> 00:31:06.534
Krem has the strength
of one thousand men.

334
00:31:06.667 --> 00:31:07.702
He'll tear
this little girl apart.

335
00:31:11.572 --> 00:31:13.140
He's on Bilquis.

336
00:31:16.077 --> 00:31:17.578
Nice try.
Bilquis's a dead planet.

337
00:31:17.712 --> 00:31:19.613
Dying. not dead.

338
00:31:19.747 --> 00:31:21.716
The atomic wars
brought destruction.

339
00:31:21.849 --> 00:31:23.617
Half the population is gone.

340
00:31:23.751 --> 00:31:26.387
And the remaining resources
have drawn filth.

341
00:31:26.520 --> 00:31:28.322
From every corner
of the galaxy.

342
00:31:28.756 --> 00:31:30.825
Filth. Like the Brigands.

343
00:31:30.958 --> 00:31:32.626
They scavenge for people.

344
00:31:34.362 --> 00:31:35.495
People?

345
00:31:38.265 --> 00:31:39.467
For girls.

346
00:31:40.334 --> 00:31:43.637
Girls to help them continue
their all-male race.

347
00:31:47.274 --> 00:31:48.342
Cool.

348
00:31:50.778 --> 00:31:52.380
So we're going to Bilquis.

349
00:32:01.956 --> 00:32:03.991
All right.
let's take you shopping.

350
00:32:05.593 --> 00:32:06.827
Perfect.

351
00:32:11.565 --> 00:32:13.534
-Don't freak out.
-Why would I?

352
00:32:16.837 --> 00:32:18.472
-I'm not freaking out.
-You're not freaking out.

353
00:32:18.606 --> 00:32:20.007
I'm not freaking out!

354
00:32:20.141 --> 00:32:21.342
Seems to me
like you're freaking out.

355
00:32:21.475 --> 00:32:23.711
-I might be freaking out.
-Okay.

356
00:32:25.679 --> 00:32:26.814
Good.

357
00:32:26.947 --> 00:32:28.215
Now you won't die.

358
00:32:43.697 --> 00:32:45.066
Whoa!

359
00:32:54.141 --> 00:32:55.576
You could have
done that sooner.

360
00:32:55.709 --> 00:32:56.877
Yep.

361
00:33:04.685 --> 00:33:06.687
-On your planet...
-Earth.

362
00:33:07.488 --> 00:33:08.989
Do others on Earth
have powers like you?

363
00:33:09.123 --> 00:33:11.526
No. it's a pretty small group
of two.

364
00:33:11.659 --> 00:33:12.793
Who's the other one?

365
00:33:12.927 --> 00:33:14.328
They call him Superman.

366
00:33:15.564 --> 00:33:16.864
I call him Clark.
He's my cousin.

367
00:33:17.665 --> 00:33:19.233
And you are Superwoman?

368
00:33:19.366 --> 00:33:20.868
I'm Supergirl.

369
00:33:21.502 --> 00:33:23.838
Are you considerably younger
than he is?

370
00:33:23.971 --> 00:33:26.941
There's. like.
ten years. give or take.

371
00:33:27.074 --> 00:33:28.909
How come he's a man?
I mean. you're--

372
00:33:29.043 --> 00:33:30.512
Move it! Out of the way.

373
00:33:34.782 --> 00:33:36.250
Let's find some Brigands.

374
00:33:55.736 --> 00:33:56.904
Thank you.

375
00:34:01.976 --> 00:34:03.210
<i>♪ Tall and tan</i>
<i>And young and lovely ♪</i>

376
00:34:03.344 --> 00:34:05.012
Sorry. we are a bit backed up.

377
00:34:05.246 --> 00:34:07.348
<i>♪ The girl from Ipanema</i>
<i>Goes walking ♪</i>

378
00:34:07.481 --> 00:34:09.150
Hi.

379
00:34:09.283 --> 00:34:14.455
<i>♪ And when she passes</i>
<i>Each one she passes goes "Ah!" ♪</i>

380
00:34:17.992 --> 00:34:20.094
<i>♪ But I watch her</i>
<i>So sadly... ♪</i>

381
00:34:22.730 --> 00:34:24.633
I know she's worth a lot
'round here.

382
00:34:24.765 --> 00:34:25.933
I'm aware.

383
00:34:27.234 --> 00:34:30.639
Let me have her
and you can walk out alive.

384
00:34:30.771 --> 00:34:32.239
Tempting.

385
00:34:34.141 --> 00:34:36.777
But just
switching subjects here.

386
00:34:37.244 --> 00:34:38.913
Do you have any information
on the Brigands?

387
00:34:39.446 --> 00:34:41.782
That sort of information's
gonna cost ya.

388
00:34:45.085 --> 00:34:46.253
I'll tell you what.

389
00:34:48.989 --> 00:34:50.224
I'll arm-wrestle you for her.

390
00:34:51.292 --> 00:34:52.159
Seriously.

391
00:34:52.293 --> 00:34:53.562
You win
and you can have us both.

392
00:34:53.694 --> 00:34:55.062
I win...

393
00:34:55.664 --> 00:34:57.464
and you can tell us
where the Brigands are.

394
00:35:03.137 --> 00:35:05.105
-Deal.
-Deal.

395
00:35:11.946 --> 00:35:14.715
How about you play with me?

396
00:35:34.969 --> 00:35:36.337
You ready?

397
00:35:43.477 --> 00:35:44.445
Okay.

398
00:35:46.213 --> 00:35:49.750
Okay. this does not look like
this is gonna end well.

399
00:35:50.552 --> 00:35:52.520
For you guys. I mean.

400
00:35:53.754 --> 00:35:54.922
Anybody want to leave?

401
00:35:55.823 --> 00:35:57.891
No? Okay.

402
00:35:58.025 --> 00:36:00.094
Ah. let's not hurt
the merchandise.

403
00:36:00.595 --> 00:36:01.929
Ruthye. sit down over there.

404
00:36:02.062 --> 00:36:03.897
I'll kill you.

405
00:36:06.735 --> 00:36:07.901
Keep playing.

406
00:36:08.603 --> 00:36:11.105
You know.
It's like the <i>Titanic.</i> Yeah.

407
00:36:11.238 --> 00:36:13.874
<i>♪ Heaven</i>
<i>I'm in heaven ♪</i>

408
00:36:15.109 --> 00:36:17.646
Okay. boys.
Fingers on triggers?

409
00:36:17.778 --> 00:36:19.413
<i>♪ And my heart beats</i>
<i>So that I can hardly speak ♪</i>

410
00:36:19.547 --> 00:36:20.914
Yeah? Okay. Let's go.

411
00:36:21.048 --> 00:36:25.419
♪ <i>And I seem to find</i>
<i>The happiness I seek ♪</i>

412
00:36:27.488 --> 00:36:29.591
<i>♪ When we're out together ♪</i>

413
00:36:29.724 --> 00:36:33.528
<i>♪ Dancing cheek to cheek ♪</i>

414
00:36:34.194 --> 00:36:39.433
<i>♪ Heaven. I'm in heaven ♪</i>

415
00:36:40.100 --> 00:36:42.970
<i>♪ And the cares</i>
<i>That hung around me ♪</i>

416
00:36:43.103 --> 00:36:45.239
<i>♪ Through the week... ♪</i>

417
00:36:45.707 --> 00:36:48.442
How was that discreet?
You broke that man's arm.

418
00:36:48.576 --> 00:36:50.712
Okay. I'm...
Look. I'm... I'm sorry.

419
00:36:50.844 --> 00:36:52.313
Okay? My dog's dying.

420
00:36:52.446 --> 00:36:53.447
so I don't really have
the patience

421
00:36:53.581 --> 00:36:56.016
that I should have right now.
Okay?

422
00:37:05.727 --> 00:37:06.827
Oh. you don't have to.

423
00:37:06.960 --> 00:37:08.429
No. no. no. no.
It's good. It's good.

424
00:37:08.563 --> 00:37:10.297
Oh. I didn't know that
you spoke the Common Tongue.

425
00:37:10.431 --> 00:37:11.365
Little.

426
00:37:16.970 --> 00:37:18.573
-Mareck.
-Mar... Mareck.

427
00:37:19.306 --> 00:37:20.374
Bomar.

428
00:37:20.508 --> 00:37:23.477
Well. we're actually here
looking for somebody.

429
00:37:23.611 --> 00:37:26.380
You don't happen to know
any Brigands? Do you?

430
00:37:37.792 --> 00:37:38.926
Shit.

431
00:37:39.993 --> 00:37:41.128
It's Lobo.

432
00:37:45.499 --> 00:37:46.735
- Who?
- Keep quiet.

433
00:37:46.867 --> 00:37:48.469
No eye contact.

434
00:37:51.472 --> 00:37:53.173
He's an immortal
with a God complex.

435
00:37:53.307 --> 00:37:55.175
Killed off his entire planet.

436
00:37:55.309 --> 00:37:57.177
Not a fun guy. Hey.

437
00:37:59.146 --> 00:38:01.549
Three more of whatever
you call that shit.

438
00:38:03.083 --> 00:38:04.251
I'm looking for a Brigand.

439
00:38:04.385 --> 00:38:06.186
Goes by the name
of Drom Baxton.

440
00:38:06.320 --> 00:38:07.388
He's an ugly friggin' bastich.

441
00:38:07.522 --> 00:38:09.256
-He's looking for Brigands.
-No!

442
00:38:09.390 --> 00:38:11.925
Red mohawk. Dead left eye.

443
00:38:16.063 --> 00:38:17.866
He's so rude.

444
00:38:18.432 --> 00:38:19.433
Have you seen him?

445
00:38:19.801 --> 00:38:20.901
No.

446
00:38:21.502 --> 00:38:24.271
I know he was here.
You're saying he wasn't?

447
00:38:24.405 --> 00:38:26.240
-I'm gonna go.
-Sit down.

448
00:38:28.041 --> 00:38:29.476
Are you calling me a liar?

449
00:38:34.348 --> 00:38:35.282
No.

450
00:38:38.318 --> 00:38:39.521
Well. I am.

451
00:38:40.921 --> 00:38:42.456
But not about this.

452
00:38:44.291 --> 00:38:45.325
He's worth a lot of money.

453
00:38:45.459 --> 00:38:47.127
Take care of my whole year.

454
00:38:50.832 --> 00:38:52.433
-Excuse me.
-Go away.

455
00:38:52.567 --> 00:38:54.368
I am Ruthye Marye Knoll
of the Danastia Clan.

456
00:38:54.501 --> 00:38:55.335
Who cares?

457
00:38:55.469 --> 00:38:57.371
And I come here
with one purpose.

458
00:38:57.504 --> 00:39:00.073
to seek revenge against
Krem of the Yellow Hills.

459
00:39:00.207 --> 00:39:02.209
We could help you
take on the Brigands.

460
00:39:02.342 --> 00:39:04.311
You're going to help me?

461
00:39:05.547 --> 00:39:07.816
Do you know
who you are speaking to?

462
00:39:10.518 --> 00:39:12.152
Would you like to find out?

463
00:39:13.220 --> 00:39:14.856
Hi! We're just
a couple of girls

464
00:39:14.988 --> 00:39:18.192
from Metropolis. USA.

465
00:39:18.325 --> 00:39:19.493
We're doing a fun little tour.

466
00:39:19.627 --> 00:39:20.929
Of space!

467
00:39:21.061 --> 00:39:23.063
It's for my... my birthday.

468
00:39:23.565 --> 00:39:24.799
Yeah. we've been on.
what is it.

469
00:39:24.933 --> 00:39:27.067
like. three planets so far?

470
00:39:27.201 --> 00:39:29.303
And I'm exhausted.

471
00:39:29.436 --> 00:39:32.339
You know?
Like. OMG. I had no idea

472
00:39:32.473 --> 00:39:34.809
that space was
so. like. vast and...

473
00:39:34.943 --> 00:39:36.210
Stop.

474
00:39:37.579 --> 00:39:40.280
You're hurting my head.

475
00:39:43.016 --> 00:39:45.118
You all have been
super useless.

476
00:39:45.920 --> 00:39:47.254
Happy birthday.

477
00:39:50.090 --> 00:39:51.726
Useless.

478
00:39:53.460 --> 00:39:56.430
We know friend know Brigands.

479
00:39:57.732 --> 00:39:59.199
Our house. meet?

480
00:39:59.333 --> 00:40:02.737
We walk.
but not safe for Ruthye.

481
00:40:03.838 --> 00:40:05.305
Wear this?

482
00:40:07.074 --> 00:40:10.010
Bomar get friend
and meet home.

483
00:40:33.166 --> 00:40:34.536
Wait here.

484
00:40:38.238 --> 00:40:41.543
Girl is tired. Rest.

485
00:40:41.676 --> 00:40:43.477
When will Bomar be here
with your friend?

486
00:40:43.611 --> 00:40:44.646
Soon.

487
00:40:48.516 --> 00:40:50.450
So. is Superman like you?

488
00:40:51.619 --> 00:40:53.655
Grumpy? Rude?

489
00:40:53.788 --> 00:40:56.056
-You think I'm rude?
-Of course.

490
00:40:56.691 --> 00:40:58.191
Seems to be something
you do intentionally.

491
00:40:58.325 --> 00:41:00.528
-Okay.
-Is Superman not that way?

492
00:41:00.662 --> 00:41:02.095
Clark? No.

493
00:41:02.229 --> 00:41:04.566
He's a freakin' nerd.

494
00:41:04.966 --> 00:41:06.099
Let's just say
we're not alike.

495
00:41:06.233 --> 00:41:08.268
-Because?
-I don't know.

496
00:41:08.402 --> 00:41:10.070
He sees the good in everyone.
and I see the truth.

497
00:41:10.203 --> 00:41:11.573
So you think he's naive?

498
00:41:11.706 --> 00:41:15.577
-No. but... He's young.
-But isn't he older than you?

499
00:41:15.710 --> 00:41:17.845
Yeah. but it's not his age
that makes him young.

500
00:41:17.979 --> 00:41:19.379
it's his heart.

501
00:41:19.514 --> 00:41:22.517
There are just some things
he never had to go through.

502
00:41:22.650 --> 00:41:25.753
So his heart is light.
you know?

503
00:41:25.887 --> 00:41:29.389
It's not like mine or Bomar's
or your--

504
00:41:38.866 --> 00:41:39.867
What's Earth like?

505
00:41:44.304 --> 00:41:46.139
I'm not really
from Earth. Ruthye.

506
00:41:47.775 --> 00:41:49.109
From another planet.

507
00:41:51.045 --> 00:41:52.179
Krypton.

508
00:41:55.783 --> 00:41:59.053
I thought everyone died
the day the core erupted.

509
00:41:59.453 --> 00:42:01.623
No. Krypton didn't die
in a day.

510
00:42:03.057 --> 00:42:04.525
The gods are not that kind.

511
00:42:09.363 --> 00:42:12.399
<i>My father</i>
<i>and his brother Jor-El</i>

512
00:42:12.533 --> 00:42:15.335
<i>tried to warn the Council</i>
<i>of what was coming...</i>

513
00:42:16.303 --> 00:42:19.073
<i>but no one listened.</i>

514
00:42:29.550 --> 00:42:30.652
Mm.

515
00:42:32.820 --> 00:42:34.889
Is it now?
I thought we had more time.

516
00:42:35.023 --> 00:42:37.925
So did I. but Krypton's core
is too unstable.

517
00:42:39.060 --> 00:42:40.293
It will explode in minutes.

518
00:42:40.695 --> 00:42:44.364
I have triggered
the force field. We need to go.

519
00:42:44.498 --> 00:42:46.000
Alura!

520
00:42:46.134 --> 00:42:48.301
Now!

521
00:42:56.176 --> 00:42:57.879
Is that him?

522
00:43:00.313 --> 00:43:01.281
That is Kal-El.

523
00:43:01.448 --> 00:43:02.684
The sweet little boy

524
00:43:02.817 --> 00:43:04.484
your brother has declared
a conqueror of worlds.

525
00:43:09.023 --> 00:43:10.692
It's time.

526
00:43:46.961 --> 00:43:49.864
<i>That was eight years</i>
<i>before I was born.</i>

527
00:44:02.176 --> 00:44:05.345
Are we fools. Zor-El?

528
00:44:05.479 --> 00:44:08.683
Should we have listened
to your brother?

529
00:44:08.816 --> 00:44:11.652
We can't send our daughter...

530
00:44:11.786 --> 00:44:14.122
to another planet
to be some sort of god.

531
00:44:14.488 --> 00:44:16.490
We preserved all this
for a reason.

532
00:44:18.126 --> 00:44:22.563
We have to believe
there's a future here.

533
00:44:28.803 --> 00:44:31.873
Kara. where are you?

534
00:44:40.948 --> 00:44:43.117
<i>Honestly. I didn't have a clue</i>

535
00:44:43.251 --> 00:44:47.255
<i>that Argo was different</i>
<i>from any other planet.</i>

536
00:44:48.923 --> 00:44:50.591
<i>I thought we were lucky.</i>

537
00:44:51.893 --> 00:44:54.294
<i>But luck.</i>
<i>almost by definition.</i>

538
00:44:54.427 --> 00:44:55.328
<i>runs out.</i>

539
00:45:05.405 --> 00:45:06.574
Tell me.

540
00:45:08.509 --> 00:45:11.112
When Argo City broke off.
it unearthed...

541
00:45:11.245 --> 00:45:15.750
a crystalline mineral
buried deep in the planet.

542
00:45:16.918 --> 00:45:17.652
Kryptonite.

543
00:45:18.886 --> 00:45:21.923
The soil has been poisoned.

544
00:45:22.223 --> 00:45:24.892
People are ill all over Argo...

545
00:45:25.059 --> 00:45:27.695
and it's spreading.

546
00:45:29.362 --> 00:45:32.399
And can it be helped?

547
00:45:48.916 --> 00:45:49.684
Kara.

548
00:45:51.451 --> 00:45:52.753
What is all this?

549
00:45:54.487 --> 00:45:58.926
Trying to preserve Argo with
my force field was a failure.

550
00:45:59.694 --> 00:46:03.831
The radiation
has taken hold of me. too.

551
00:46:05.633 --> 00:46:07.535
I cannot let it get you.

552
00:46:11.239 --> 00:46:14.441
I found my brother's sketches
for the escape pod.

553
00:46:15.343 --> 00:46:16.878
I made it big enough for you.

554
00:46:18.512 --> 00:46:20.948
You will follow your cousin.
Kal-El.

555
00:46:22.449 --> 00:46:25.519
You will make a new home
on Earth.

556
00:46:28.222 --> 00:46:28.923
No!

557
00:46:30.524 --> 00:46:31.959
This is my home.

558
00:46:32.526 --> 00:46:36.429
This is my only home.

559
00:46:38.733 --> 00:46:41.535
Let the radiation take me too.

560
00:46:42.136 --> 00:46:46.073
I'll lie in the ground
next to you and next to mom.

561
00:46:49.677 --> 00:46:51.913
I am one tiny life.

562
00:46:52.780 --> 00:46:56.550
What difference does it make
whether I live or die?

563
00:46:56.684 --> 00:46:59.887
You are not one tiny life.

564
00:47:00.788 --> 00:47:03.858
You are your mother's life.

565
00:47:05.026 --> 00:47:07.028
You are my life.

566
00:47:07.895 --> 00:47:11.666
You are our souls
unfolding into the future.

567
00:47:12.733 --> 00:47:14.201
My child...

568
00:47:14.702 --> 00:47:17.705
this is why you must live.

569
00:47:30.217 --> 00:47:31.919
When I am gone.

570
00:47:33.154 --> 00:47:37.024
I need you
to promise me something.

571
00:47:37.725 --> 00:47:39.026
Of course. mother.

572
00:47:40.761 --> 00:47:42.930
Just be good.

573
00:47:43.064 --> 00:47:47.268
That doesn't mean
you cannot be tough.

574
00:47:47.401 --> 00:47:50.838
And that doesn't mean
you have to be nice.

575
00:47:53.207 --> 00:47:55.076
But you must be good.

576
00:48:04.085 --> 00:48:06.854
We do not choose our paths.

577
00:48:08.723 --> 00:48:11.258
Your path
will be one of great effort...

578
00:48:13.527 --> 00:48:15.930
of great purpose.

579
00:48:17.798 --> 00:48:22.937
Where you are going.
you will have enormous power.

580
00:48:24.572 --> 00:48:25.806
Use it to protect those...

581
00:48:25.940 --> 00:48:28.142
who cannot protect themselves.

582
00:48:29.777 --> 00:48:31.645
Trust yourself...

583
00:48:31.979 --> 00:48:33.614
to know what is right. Kara.

584
00:49:15.322 --> 00:49:16.724
We are with you.

585
00:49:50.925 --> 00:49:52.159
So. yeah.

586
00:49:54.929 --> 00:49:55.963
When I say
I know what it's like.

587
00:49:56.097 --> 00:49:58.265
I'm not talking
out of my ass. Ruthye.

588
00:49:58.399 --> 00:50:00.067
Grief is a killer. You know?

589
00:50:00.201 --> 00:50:02.103
It can make you want
to break bad. or...

590
00:50:03.170 --> 00:50:05.039
you know. get revenge. but...

591
00:50:08.275 --> 00:50:09.310
I don't think
any of those things

592
00:50:09.443 --> 00:50:11.612
are gonna lead you
to where you want to go.

593
00:50:15.382 --> 00:50:16.383
So. what does?

594
00:50:18.085 --> 00:50:20.054
When did you stop
feeling angry?

595
00:50:22.323 --> 00:50:23.891
Any day now.

596
00:50:40.141 --> 00:50:41.408
Um...

597
00:50:41.543 --> 00:50:43.043
I'm just gonna
go check on him.

598
00:50:43.811 --> 00:50:45.379
Stay here.

599
00:51:15.109 --> 00:51:16.277
Where's your friend?

600
00:51:16.410 --> 00:51:18.679
They come now. Sit.

601
00:51:32.426 --> 00:51:34.862
Recipe from my mother.

602
00:51:34.995 --> 00:51:37.064
from her mother.
mother. mother...

603
00:51:38.633 --> 00:51:41.368
-A little bitter.
-Thank you.

604
00:51:42.436 --> 00:51:43.404
Drink.

605
00:51:54.516 --> 00:51:56.116
How does your friend
know the Brigands?

606
00:51:58.520 --> 00:52:01.088
We all know the Brigands.

607
00:52:03.357 --> 00:52:04.191
But you said--

608
00:52:04.325 --> 00:52:07.562
Brigands come here.
take girls.

609
00:52:07.696 --> 00:52:10.965
They come here.
take... our girl.

610
00:52:13.434 --> 00:52:14.468
Sarna.

611
00:52:15.936 --> 00:52:19.273
Yeah. your. um...
your daughter. the...

612
00:52:19.907 --> 00:52:21.375
The pictures.

613
00:52:23.744 --> 00:52:25.346
What did you give me?

614
00:52:26.113 --> 00:52:27.982
Sorry. Sorry. stop drinking.
Stop drinking.

615
00:52:28.115 --> 00:52:29.183
Bomar. stop!

616
00:52:29.316 --> 00:52:31.318
It's for our daughter.
we have no choice.

617
00:52:31.452 --> 00:52:33.254
Did you get
this poison from the Brigands?

618
00:52:33.387 --> 00:52:36.658
I-- No understand.
You should be...

619
00:52:36.790 --> 00:52:38.292
Paralyzed.

620
00:52:38.425 --> 00:52:40.294
This is just
really gonna suck.

621
00:52:42.631 --> 00:52:44.098
Ow.

622
00:52:46.367 --> 00:52:47.801
Whoa.

623
00:52:51.939 --> 00:52:53.340
- Milk.
- Why?

624
00:52:53.474 --> 00:52:56.477
Well. it coats your stomach
if you've been poisoned.

625
00:52:56.611 --> 00:52:57.712
Come on. man.

626
00:52:57.845 --> 00:52:59.146
It's a white liquid.

627
00:52:59.280 --> 00:53:00.914
-Door. Door.
-Help me out here.

628
00:53:09.189 --> 00:53:10.592
What kind of milk
was that?

629
00:53:10.725 --> 00:53:11.925
Chewchan.

630
00:53:12.527 --> 00:53:13.628
Chewchan.

631
00:53:13.762 --> 00:53:15.664
Oh. my God. Okay.

632
00:53:16.196 --> 00:53:17.364
So. you sold me out...
for what?

633
00:53:17.498 --> 00:53:20.100
What are you... What are you
getting in return?

634
00:53:20.234 --> 00:53:21.402
Speak.

635
00:53:21.802 --> 00:53:24.104
One girl for two girls.

636
00:53:56.870 --> 00:53:57.838
Hello.

637
00:54:01.842 --> 00:54:03.010
Are you okay?

638
00:54:06.380 --> 00:54:08.415
I heard
you were looking for me.

639
00:54:08.550 --> 00:54:09.751
Huh?

640
00:54:12.019 --> 00:54:13.521
You found me.

641
00:54:13.655 --> 00:54:15.456
Technically. you found me.

642
00:54:26.634 --> 00:54:27.935
Mm.

643
00:54:42.650 --> 00:54:45.553
Hey. man. Can you just give me
one second?

644
00:54:56.230 --> 00:54:58.432
Thanks. I needed that.

645
00:55:14.314 --> 00:55:17.685
You dropped
your puppy's antidote.

646
00:55:21.955 --> 00:55:23.056
Kara!

647
00:55:25.527 --> 00:55:26.994
Help me!

648
00:55:29.062 --> 00:55:30.330
Help!

649
00:55:33.535 --> 00:55:35.135
No!

650
00:55:36.470 --> 00:55:37.404
Kara!

651
00:55:45.112 --> 00:55:46.648
Come on!

652
00:55:53.987 --> 00:55:55.255
Whoa!

653
00:55:57.826 --> 00:55:59.126
Sorry!

654
00:56:01.930 --> 00:56:03.430
-Are you drunk?
-No!

655
00:56:08.837 --> 00:56:10.304
Hey.

656
00:56:10.437 --> 00:56:12.540
She don't look very poisoned
to me. eh?

657
00:56:14.208 --> 00:56:15.309
Bring me their daughter.

658
00:56:15.442 --> 00:56:16.644
Now.

659
00:56:17.077 --> 00:56:18.078
You smell of vomit.

660
00:56:18.212 --> 00:56:19.814
Because Mareck poisoned me.

661
00:56:20.481 --> 00:56:22.851
Oh. and I am fine.
thank you for asking.

662
00:56:43.470 --> 00:56:44.404
Huh.

663
00:56:51.078 --> 00:56:52.614
The brides!

664
00:56:52.747 --> 00:56:53.648
Get them! Get them!

665
00:56:57.451 --> 00:56:58.686
Don't move.

666
00:57:32.787 --> 00:57:33.755
Run.

667
00:57:47.067 --> 00:57:48.402
Drom Baxton.

668
00:57:49.003 --> 00:57:51.071
There's a lot of rich dipshits
looking for you.

669
00:57:51.204 --> 00:57:52.740
Screw you. old man.

670
00:57:55.175 --> 00:57:56.544
Shit.

671
00:58:09.356 --> 00:58:11.626
-Sarna! Sarna!
-Sarna! Sarna! Sarna!

672
00:58:11.759 --> 00:58:13.327
A deal is a deal.

673
00:58:14.194 --> 00:58:15.362
She has to die.

674
00:58:15.495 --> 00:58:17.130
- No!
- Sarna!

675
00:58:36.183 --> 00:58:37.417
Ouch.

676
00:58:45.593 --> 00:58:46.995
Aren't you the ditz
from that dive bar?

677
00:58:47.127 --> 00:58:48.062
Funny.

678
00:58:48.863 --> 00:58:50.031
That's what
I've been calling you.

679
00:58:50.163 --> 00:58:51.298
Touché!

680
00:59:56.531 --> 00:59:58.365
Oh. that's ballsy.

681
00:59:58.498 --> 01:00:01.135
Drom Baxton!
You just made me angry.

682
01:00:11.512 --> 01:00:12.647
Got you. bastich.

683
01:00:22.355 --> 01:00:24.257
Sarna.

684
01:00:26.094 --> 01:00:28.096
Where are you?

685
01:00:28.529 --> 01:00:30.932
You okay? Yeah?
Okay. get her out of here.

686
01:00:31.065 --> 01:00:33.500
She's the last one. Go. Go!

687
01:00:48.348 --> 01:00:51.185
Come on. Krem.
Where's my antidote?

688
01:00:51.753 --> 01:00:53.721
You like to play games.

689
01:00:54.889 --> 01:00:56.858
I can play games.

690
01:01:03.631 --> 01:01:06.868
I can smell you.

691
01:01:25.620 --> 01:01:27.021
-I told you not to move.
-I had him.

692
01:01:27.155 --> 01:01:28.455
Hide.

693
01:01:34.228 --> 01:01:35.395
Shit!

694
01:01:37.865 --> 01:01:38.833
Sarna!

695
01:01:42.703 --> 01:01:43.971
Bye-bye.

696
01:01:44.371 --> 01:01:45.807
No! No!

697
01:02:18.840 --> 01:02:20.241
They're dead.

698
01:02:20.373 --> 01:02:22.610
Because you did not let me do
what had to be done!

699
01:02:22.743 --> 01:02:24.745
Okay. Ruthye. I'm not
letting you kill that man.

700
01:02:24.879 --> 01:02:27.480
Why not? Look at the suffering
he leaves in his wake.

701
01:02:27.615 --> 01:02:29.250
Why does he get to be alive?
Why?

702
01:02:29.382 --> 01:02:30.952
Okay! Okay. stop freaking out!

703
01:02:31.085 --> 01:02:34.522
Get off! Don't tell me
not to freak out.

704
01:02:34.655 --> 01:02:36.324
I'm allowed.

705
01:02:36.456 --> 01:02:37.592
Tell me why.

706
01:02:37.725 --> 01:02:39.392
Because it'll mess you up.

707
01:02:39.794 --> 01:02:42.395
You think it will make you
feel better? It won't.

708
01:02:42.763 --> 01:02:44.665
It'll haunt you
for the rest of your life.

709
01:02:44.799 --> 01:02:46.100
Is that what you want?

710
01:02:48.002 --> 01:02:49.837
So. the alternative
is to be like you?

711
01:02:50.738 --> 01:02:52.372
Constantly leaving your planet

712
01:02:52.505 --> 01:02:53.641
to drink yourself
into a stupor?

713
01:02:54.642 --> 01:02:55.843
Drunk all of the time

714
01:02:55.977 --> 01:02:57.612
so you never
have to feel anything?

715
01:02:57.745 --> 01:03:00.548
Guess what? I too want
to free myself of this pain.

716
01:03:00.915 --> 01:03:02.583
And I do not want
to be like you.

717
01:03:03.517 --> 01:03:04.685
Okay.

718
01:03:05.820 --> 01:03:07.121
Then why don't you go find

719
01:03:07.255 --> 01:03:09.257
whatever dimensional portal
he just passed through

720
01:03:09.389 --> 01:03:10.925
all by yourself?

721
01:04:31.973 --> 01:04:33.374
Hey! Squidward!

722
01:04:33.506 --> 01:04:34.442
Where are the Brigands?

723
01:04:34.575 --> 01:04:36.243
-No idea.
-Really?

724
01:04:36.377 --> 01:04:38.145
-Aargh!
-Bullshit.

725
01:04:38.279 --> 01:04:40.948
I have less than 24 hours
to save my dog.

726
01:04:41.082 --> 01:04:42.850
so you tell me
where the Brigands are

727
01:04:42.984 --> 01:04:45.586
and I won't turn you
into a hand puppet. Okay?

728
01:04:45.720 --> 01:04:47.021
Okay.

729
01:04:51.759 --> 01:04:55.663
Okay.
But you'll have to wear this.

730
01:05:01.369 --> 01:05:02.403
Let's go.

731
01:05:37.805 --> 01:05:39.607
This is as close as we get.

732
01:06:49.243 --> 01:06:50.244
Hi. there.

733
01:06:53.013 --> 01:06:54.648
I've been tracking your ship
for the last month.

734
01:06:54.782 --> 01:06:57.084
I believe you're from Krypton?

735
01:06:57.218 --> 01:06:58.219
And so am I.

736
01:07:00.121 --> 01:07:01.455
Clark.

737
01:07:02.289 --> 01:07:03.691
I don't understand you.

738
01:07:04.325 --> 01:07:05.626
Where am I?

739
01:07:05.860 --> 01:07:07.962
Is this Earth?

740
01:07:08.896 --> 01:07:10.131
Are you Kal-El?

741
01:07:10.264 --> 01:07:12.333
I'm sorry. I don't...

742
01:07:12.466 --> 01:07:13.367
I don't. um...

743
01:07:14.435 --> 01:07:15.503
I don't speak Kryptonian.

744
01:07:15.636 --> 01:07:16.804
I didn't ever...

745
01:07:17.371 --> 01:07:19.874
Shoot. I...
I wasn't raised there. so...

746
01:07:20.007 --> 01:07:20.941
I wasn't raised there!

747
01:07:21.075 --> 01:07:22.209
Why am I talking louder?

748
01:07:22.343 --> 01:07:23.545
Let me help you.

749
01:07:23.677 --> 01:07:25.279
Krypto. be good. buddy.

750
01:07:26.180 --> 01:07:27.047
Be good.

751
01:07:27.181 --> 01:07:28.082
He's a feisty little guy.

752
01:07:28.215 --> 01:07:30.084
He's cute.

753
01:07:31.018 --> 01:07:32.253
Is it okay if I...

754
01:07:37.526 --> 01:07:38.692
Watch your step there.

755
01:07:39.460 --> 01:07:40.961
Might be slippery. so...

756
01:07:41.095 --> 01:07:43.197
Is this... I'll grab it.

757
01:07:44.698 --> 01:07:45.866
Okay.

758
01:07:46.834 --> 01:07:48.936
Ah. yeah. Pretty cool. huh?

759
01:07:50.971 --> 01:07:52.907
Don't worry.
we don't actually live here.

760
01:07:53.340 --> 01:07:55.376
There's a lot more to Earth
than just this place.

761
01:07:56.611 --> 01:07:58.613
Big city. Lots of stuff to do.

762
01:07:58.746 --> 01:08:00.615
Bowling. that's fun.

763
01:08:00.748 --> 01:08:02.116
It was a big adjustment
for me.

764
01:08:02.249 --> 01:08:03.250
You know. coming from Kansas.

765
01:08:03.384 --> 01:08:05.554
You know.
small town kinda guy. but...

766
01:08:05.686 --> 01:08:06.921
You know Kansas?

767
01:08:07.054 --> 01:08:08.722
No. Why would you know Kansas?

768
01:08:08.856 --> 01:08:11.258
What am I...?

769
01:08:11.392 --> 01:08:13.460
You can't understand a word
that I'm saying right now.

770
01:08:15.597 --> 01:08:17.932
It's okay. You will one day.

771
01:08:18.332 --> 01:08:21.268
And you'll also learn to love
this place just like I have.

772
01:08:22.303 --> 01:08:23.304
Promise.

773
01:08:27.007 --> 01:08:28.842
Why is he in his underwear?

774
01:08:28.976 --> 01:08:30.444
Oh.
Should mention.

775
01:08:32.379 --> 01:08:35.650
Your powers are gonna start
kicking in right about...

776
01:08:35.783 --> 01:08:36.850
now.

777
01:08:51.298 --> 01:08:53.067
How can this be home?

778
01:09:58.533 --> 01:10:00.367
I thought that the shelter
might help.

779
01:10:00.769 --> 01:10:01.770
Was I right?

780
01:10:01.902 --> 01:10:03.003
Wait...

781
01:10:03.837 --> 01:10:04.938
What did you...

782
01:10:05.072 --> 01:10:06.173
I saw you boarding
that man's ship.

783
01:10:06.307 --> 01:10:08.008
so I snuck up
into the cargo hold.

784
01:10:08.909 --> 01:10:09.977
What's this place?

785
01:10:14.081 --> 01:10:15.983
It's my prison.

786
01:10:16.116 --> 01:10:19.486
The Brigands know that
the planet orbits between...

787
01:10:20.454 --> 01:10:21.523
two suns.

788
01:10:23.090 --> 01:10:24.825
And that the green sun...

789
01:10:26.093 --> 01:10:27.261
can kill me.

790
01:10:31.065 --> 01:10:33.834
Krem left your ship on Bilquis
